<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXY-NOTEBOOK-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DATE SET FOR U.S. OPEN CUP SEMIFINAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ The Galaxy learned Saturday that it will host
the Chicago Fire at Cal State Fullerton on Aug. 23 in the
semifinals of the Lamar Hunt U.S. Open Cup.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles, which will take on the Fire twice in a span of five
days, will travel to Chicago on Aug. 19 for a regular season MLS
game.
</P>
<P>
   This is only the second time the Galaxy has participated in the
Open Cup, a tournament that started in 1914 and is open to all
affiliated amateur and professional teams in the U.S.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy lost last season in the quarterfinals to the Columbus
Crew.
</P>
<P>
   The winner of the Chicago-L.A. game faces the winner of the New
York/New Jersey-Miami match Oct. 22 at a site to be determined. The
winner of the Open Cup earns $100,000 in prize money while the
runner-up picks up $50,000.
</P>
<P>
   A week earlier, the MLS championship takes place, meaning
there's a good chance two of the four teams left in the Open Cup
could have to play championship games in back-to-back weeks.
</P>
<P>
   HERNANDEZ OUT: Luis Hernandez will miss Wednesday's game against
Colorado because of Mexico's World Cup qualifying match against
Canada on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   He's not the only one missing. Ezra Hendrickson (St. Vincent and
the Grenadines), Mauricio Cienfuegos (El Salvador) and Cobi Jones
(U.S.) will also miss the match because of qualifying games.
</P>
<P>
   After a slow start, Hernandez has come on strong, scoring a goal
and setting up two others in last week's 5-1 victory over Kansas
City at Arrowhead Stadium. Since going without a point in his first
seven games, Hernandez has built a five-game scoring streak. He has
three goals and five assists for 11 points during that span.
</P>
<P>
   HOT STREAK II: Cienfuegos has also hit his stride. After going
13 straight games without a point, he has recorded three goals and
three assists in his last five games. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-13-00 0204EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
