<HEADLINE>
DEMOCRATS SHUN PLAYBOY CROWD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; LOS ANGELES _ At the Playboy Mansion, where the silicone
outweighed the barbecued shrimp, the talk was on - what else - the
Playboy Mansion.
</P>
<P>
   It certainly seemed like a suitable environment for a
fund-raiser - or most any other event, for that matter. The elegant
manor in Holmby Hills was softly lighted Saturday for an
invitation-only ``Welcome to L.A.'' bash for several hundred
Playboy writers, models and associates of the magazine.
</P>
<P>
   If there were any delegates or stray members of the Democratic
Party, they were keeping an extremely low profile.
</P>
<P>
   However, some media figures in the crowd were happy to talk
about the flap that led to U.S. Rep. Loretta Sanchez moving her
Tuesday fund-raiser from the mansion to B.B. King's Blues Club at
Universal City's CityWalk under pressure from the party.
</P>
<P>
   ``If the Democrats wanted to give me something to rip on night
after night, they gave me an issue that moved to the top of the
list,'' said Bill Maher, host of ABC-TV's ``Politically
Incorrect.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Of course there's nothing to be ashamed about being here. It's
just hypocrisy.''
</P>
<P>
   Although the bunnies were out in force Saturday, none were
expected to show up for Sanchez's event in the Valley.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Playboy Mansion is not Sodom and Gomorrah,'' said
Playboy's director of communications, Bill Farley. ``It has been
used by charities, for fund-raiser events, for all sorts of events.
The DNC's action really amounts to a bunch of rich white guys
picking on a Latina.''
</P>
<P>
   Farley added that few politicians were on the guest list
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Political commentator Arianna Huffington blasted the DNC for
pressuring Sanchez.
</P>
<P>
   ``Here we are having the convention in the capital of poverty in
America and the DNC is getting upset over the Playboy Mansion,''
she said. ``What goes against family values is their fund raising.
That's immoral, far more immoral than having a party in this
beautiful place.''
</P>
<P>
   Local talk radio personality Michael Jackson called the DNC's
stand ``stupidity and bungling. It's almost as if they have a death
wish. Loretta Sanchez wasn't here for the Democratic Party. She was
here for a Hispanic voters' event. This is a gorgeous setting for
any sort of party.''
</P>
<P>
   As the band played Dixieland jazz and guests began moving toward
the desert buffet, Bunnyhutch chief Hugh Hefner found a table with
five of his models.
</P>
<P>
   ``The `D' in Democrat is supposed to represent diversity,''
Hefner said. ``The fact that higher-ups in the party would attack
her in this way is just ridiculous. It really has to do with
(presumptive presidential nominee Al) Gore trying to separate
himself from the Clinton scandal. Nobody in America (likes)
bullies. One expects more from them.''
</P>
