<P>
   TAX-REFORM _ ATLANTA _ There's been much ado about tax reform
this year. The marriage tax bill has been vetoed. Estate tax repeal
hasn't gotten its veto yet. This election year has also produced
legislation, still in Congress, that would allow bigger retirement
plan contributions and cut taxes on Social Security benefits. It's
a lot for taxpayers to think about. Or it will be if our elected
leaders ever get together enough to finally approve something.
Meanwhile, a lot of Americans not only want to understand any new
provisions but to begin updating their family's financial plans.
