   MUSIC-SATELLITES (Undated) _ Delivering simultaneous streams of
music to thousands or millions of listeners over an increasingly
clogged Internet has become increasingly frustrating. If the audio
stream hits too many traffic jams, the listener may find his
Internet radio program stuttering or stopping halfway through a
song. One promising remedy involves sending the stream up to a
space satellite, hopping over most of the jam-ups on the ground and
landing the music stream at a network hub closer to the listener.
By Theresa Foley.
