   CVN-CONVENTION-RDP (Los Angeles) _ President Clinton plans to
make his Monday night speech to the Democratic Natonal Convention a
thumping defense of his eight years in office. Meanwhile, Sen.
Joseph Lieberman, D-Conn., tells an interviewer that the Senate
should have rebuked Clinton for obstructing justice in the
aftermath of his affair with former White House intern Monica
Lewinsky. By STEWART M. POWELL.
