music over the Internet, concerns the vibrant, commerce-driven
world of pop music. Napster has grown into a national fad by
offering free tunes and a sense of community for a youthful,
computer-savvy crowd _ underscored by the rebellious thrill of
ripping off major corporations. This is not the profile of the
typical classical music fan. While a smattering of pieces by Bach
and Brahms, Stravinsky and Steve Reich are available on Napster,
downloaded music has thus far had a negligible effect on classical
recordings.(Ruhe, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
