Bumiller and Bernard Weinraub.
</P>
<P>
   DEM-CHAIRMAN-PROFILE (Washington) _ Profile of Joe Andrew,
Democratic convention chairman. By Melinda Henneberger.
</P>
<P>
   DEM-SCHEDULE (Undated) _ Opening day schedule.
</P>
<P>
   DEM-WIRED (Los Angeles) _ Picture the scene on the convention
floor in Los Angeles. There are Democratic delegates galore with
banners and balloons, funny hats and confetti. And, of course,
computers. And Palm Pilots, digital cameras, wireless beepers and
all sorts of other high-tech gadgets to showcase the party's
technological prowess and burnish its party-of-the-future image.
``We've basically wired the entire city of Los Angeles,'' said Naz
Nageer, director of technology for the Democratic National
Convention Committee. By Leslie Wayne.
</P>
<P>
   DEM-PLAYBOY (Los Angeles) _ By most measures, Hugh Hefner and
his daughter, Christie, are hardly the largest donors to the
Democratic Party. But, this week, as a controversy swirled around
the use of the Playboy Mansion for a Hispanic fund-raiser, they
became, for a moment, among the most visible. By Leslie Wayne.
</P>
