   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-PUTIN (Moscow) _ Since becoming president of Russia,
Vladimir Putin has capitalized on a voter mandate and high poll
ratings to begin putting Russia back in order after a decade of
wild economic and political swings. But along the way, he is
breaking a lot of china, indulging some of the anti-democratic
instincts, his critics say, that came with his KGB training. By
Patrick E. Tyler.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
