<HEADLINE>
WNBA FLOOR SHOW HEATS UP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; The 10 finalists are the Sparks' Lisa Leslie, Houston's Sheryl
Swoops, Utah's Jennifer Azzi, Miami's Mi Flores, Portland's
Michelle Marciniak, Washington's Nikki McCray, Orlando coach/GM
Carolyn Peck and Phoenix's Michelle Griffiths, Lisa Harrison and
Maria Stepanova.
</P>
<P>
   Is it the ballot for the WNBA's Most Inspirational?
</P>
<P>
   Kind of.
</P>
<P>
   They qualified as the ``10 Hottest Women of the WNBA'' featured
in a Playboy.com poll (www.playboy.com/sports/features/wnba/index
.html) that asks fans to cast their vote through Aug. 25 for who
should be No. &UR;  &LR; 1.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, it's sexist. But Phoenix coach Cheryl Miller doesn't
seem to care.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm a huge fan of just filling the seats, and if it takes the
Anna Kournikovas of the world to fill them, then that's what you
have to do,'' Miller said. ``I don't want to focus on (looks) being
the main draw because there's a lot of talented players in the
WNBA, but hey, whatever fills the seats.''
</P>
<P>
   Or entices folks to log on.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; __  &LR; An ESPN.com poll conducted the day Jerry West resigned
asked users ``Who is the greatest Laker of all time?''
</P>
<P>
   Out of nearly 100,000 votes, West came in a distant fourth (10.2
percent), behind Magic Johnson (41.4), Wilt Chamberlain (22.9) and
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar (21.7).
</P>
<P>
   &UR; __  &LR; The Golf Channel's site (www.thegolfchannel.com) leads the
charge of PGA Championship-related activity this week when is
stages a massive relaunch today.
</P>
<P>
   This site will be one of at least three trying to make sure
every Tiger Woods move is noted. TGC uses a device called ``Where's
Tiger Now?'' that marks where each of his shots lands on the
fairway, checks driving distance and illustrates his shot-selection
process. CNNSI.com and MSNBC.com also have tracking devices on
Woods.
</P>
</TEXT>
