<HEADLINE>
KINGS SIGN SCHNEIDER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ Mathieu Schneider, the former New York Islanders
captain and top defensive scorer last season with the New York
Rangers, agreed Sunday to a one-year, $2.1 million contract with
the Kings.
</P>
<P>
   With the loss of Garry Galley and Sean O'Donnell during the
offseason, the Kings made defense a priority this summer.
Schneider, 31, is expected to team with Kings captain Rob Blake on
the first unit, with Mattias Norstrom moving back to play with
either Aki Berg, Jere Karalahti or one of several young defensemen
drafted or acquired through free agency.
</P>
<P>
   Although Schneider, who also holds an option for the 2001-2002
season, played with Kings top winger Ziggy Palffy on the Islanders,
it was his relationship with Blake that helped close the deal.
</P>
<P>
   ``I had been coming out to L.A. the past few years to work out
with (Blake) at Gold's Gym in Venice Beach, so there was a really
good feeling coming in,'' Schneider said by phone from his New York
City home. ``There is a good chance for a lot of ice time and work
on the power play.''
</P>
<P>
   Schneider led Rangers defensemen last season with 30 points (10
goals, 20 assists) and 78 penalty minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
