<P>
   AFRICAN-AMERICAN-FILMS (Undated) _ The spate of black films this
summer may be the biggest sign yet of a new era. At the same time
that young white kids _ N'Sync, Britney Spears and Eminem _ are
tearing up the pop charts by appropriating hiphop and soul,
black-themed movies have made a run at the audiences who are buying
that music. A Critic's Notebook by Elvis Mitchell.
